               <p>My husband is a <rs id="t17900224-39-viclabel227" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900224-39-victim404 t17900224-39-viclabel227"></join>: I lost these gowns off the horse by the fire-place; I saw the prisoner take them: I live at <placeName id="t17900224-39-crimeloc228">No. 1, Chapel-street, Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17900224-39-crimeloc228" type="placeName" value="No. 1, Chapel-street, Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17900224-39-crimeloc228" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900224-39-off225 t17900224-39-crimeloc228"></join>: the parlour where they were stolen from, was on the ground floor; it was on the 29th of January, Friday, about seven in the evening; he took them with a stick; he opened the parlour door; I thought it was my<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179002240044"></xptr>husband; and in a moment he dragged the things off the horse; I ran immediately after him; when he found I was so close, he took the things and threw them down a cellar; I saw him stopped; he said to me, he was only walking past the door: the things were picked up by Mrs. Saunders, and given to me: I gave them to the constable, Whiteway.</p>
               <p>How soon did you see them after the man was stopped? - Immediately.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17900224-39-person406">
